			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Apples and oranges. The Super NES memory map has 95 Mbit devoted to the cartridge: $400000-$7DFFFF, $C00000-$FFFFFF, and every second 32 KiB part of $008000-$3FFFFF and $808000-$BFFFFF. The Sega Genesis memory map, by contrast, has only 32 Mbit for the cartridge: $000000-$3FFFFF. ($400000-$9FFFFF is &quot;Sega reserved&quot; for the Sega CD and 32X accessories.) Accessing more than 32 Mbit requires a mapper.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
